    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Engine Electrical Components - Description of Engine Electrical Components -
        Engine Mounted - CMP Sensor (Camshaft Position)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.2.2" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CMP Sensor (Camshaft Position)</title>
        <figure id="e3001106" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd09/D0947.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>CMP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>A magnetic pickup that is mounted on the left side of the lower crankcase near the front cover of the
            engine. The CMP sensor provides the ECM with a signal that indicates camshaft position. As the cam rotates,
            the sensor identifies the position of the cam by locating a peg on the cam.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
